                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 30
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    green string is sewn into the top edge of <locus target="#1 #51 #81 #99"/>;
                    green and red string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#127 #148"/>;
                    black string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#140"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#18r #36v #37v #57r #57v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#51v #131v"/>);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#35v #82v #111v"/>)
                    </desc>
